Rating: 4
This was really easy and the flavours were fantastic. You could taste each ingredient individually - the ginger, soy sauce, red-wine vinegar - and yet the whole dressing melded together very nicely. I skipped the salt because I found the dressing to be salty enough. I used too much honey mustard, which was a bit overpowering and made the dressing a bit too sweet. I usually avoid vegetable oil and make everything with olive oil, but I am glad I used vegetable oil this time. Olive oil would have ruined the flavours. In all it took about 5 minutes to make and I had all the ingredients on hand. I even used the extra dressing to put over my chicken. I think it would be a great dipping sauce for chicken fingers if you wanted something a little more sophisticated.

Rating: 4
This dressing is always a big hit! I mix it with cut up cabbage and it makes a terrific and easy cole slaw. Instead of using store bought honey mustard, I use about 1TBS dijon and 1TBS agave nectar (similar to honey but sweeter). Then I tweak it by adding either more mustard or agave depending on whether it needs to be sweeter or spicier.

